Effective Date: 25-05-2025

This privacy policy describes how the Gmail Spam Filter Chrome extension the extension handles your information.

1. Information We Access
The extension uses Google OAuth 2.0 to access your Gmail inbox using the following scope:

https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.readonly

This permission allows the extension to read email content to detect and classify spam messages.

2. How We Use Information
The extension uses email data only to analyze and highlight potential spam messages. No data is stored, saved, or shared externally.

3. Data Retention
The extension does not store or retain any personal or email data after processing. All analysis is done in real-time.

4. Third-Party Sharing
We do not share your data with third parties under any circumstances.

5. Your Consent
By using the extension, you consent to the access of your Gmail inbox for spam classification purposes.

6. Contact Us
For questions or concerns, contact: ehsaasnahata@gmail.com
